OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FMet commissioner defends   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fthin blue line badge ban   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Met Police Commissioner Sir Mark Rowley
OL,6, has defended his decision to ban       
OL,7, officers from wearing the thin blue    
OL,8, line badge.                            
OL,10,FThe badge was created as a "mark of    
OL,11,Fremembrance and respect" for officers  
OL,12,Fwho have died while working.           
OL,14,FSir Mark told City Hall's Police and   
OL,15,FCrime Committee that he was "cautious" 
OL,16,Fabout officers "showing allegiance to  
OL,17,Fany cause" on their uniform.           
OL,19,FSusan Hall, Conservative AM, called the
OL,20,Fdecision "a mistake".                  
